<subSubSection pageId="96" pageNumber="97" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="96.[151,1437,995,1821]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,995,1021]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Remarks.</emphasis>
The classification of 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, H. B." box="[540,713,995,1021]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="205 - 346" refId="ref72823" refString="Baker, H. B. (1941 a) Zonitid snails from Pacific Islands Part 3: Genera other than Microcystinae. Bernice P. Bishop Museum Bulletin, 166, 205 - 346." type="journal article" year="1941">Baker (1941a)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Solem, A." box="[777,941,995,1021]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref77598" refString="Solem, A. (1966) Some non-marine mollusks from Thailand, with notes on classification of the Helicarionidae. Spolia Zoologica Musei Hauniensis, 24, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1966">Solem (1966)</bibRefCitation>
is followed here in the inclusion of this group as a subfamily of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1883" box="[435,605,1035,1061]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Ariophantidae</taxonomicName>
, while 
<bibRefCitation author="Schileyko, A. A." box="[690,907,1035,1061]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" refId="ref76904" refString="Schileyko, A. A. (2002 b) Treatise on Recent Terrestrial Pulmonate Molluscs, Part 9: Helicarionidae, Gymnarionidae, Rhysotinidae, Ariophantidae. Ruthenica, Supplement 2, Moscow." type="book" year="2002">Schileyko (2002b)</bibRefCitation>
treated it as a tribe of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zilch" baseAuthorityYear="1959" box="[1169,1341,1035,1061]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="96" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ariophantinae">Ariophantinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="96.[151,1437,995,1821]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
As well as 
<taxonomicName authority="Benson, 1832" authorityName="Benson" authorityYear="1832" box="[328,757,1075,1101]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" genus="Macrochlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis box="[328,583,1075,1100]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Macrochlamys indica</emphasis>
Benson, 1832
</taxonomicName>
, we tentatively include 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gould, 1844)" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[1041,1431,1075,1101]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" genus="Sesara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="infrendens">
<emphasis box="[1041,1253,1075,1100]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Sesara infrendens</emphasis>
(Gould, 1844)
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[196,246,1115,1141]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Albers" authorityYear="1860" box="[385,465,1115,1140]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" genus="Sesara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[385,465,1115,1140]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Sesara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1888" box="[686,916,1115,1141]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Macrochlamydinae">Macrochlamydinae</taxonomicName>
. This latter species was not included in the phylogenetic analysis because only juvenile specimens were available. However, dissection showed that it possesses a folded epiphallic retractor caecum, appearing very similar to the coiled retractor caecum that is one of the synapomorphies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1888" box="[504,734,1235,1261]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Macrochlamydinae">Macrochlamydinae</taxonomicName>
. The only other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Albers" authorityYear="1860" box="[1045,1125,1235,1260]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" genus="Sesara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1045,1125,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Sesara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for which anatomical data are known, 
<taxonomicName authority="Solem, 1966" authorityName="Solem" authorityYear="1966" box="[289,604,1275,1301]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" genus="Sesara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="parva">
<emphasis box="[289,445,1275,1300]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Sesara parva</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Solem, A." box="[452,604,1275,1301]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref77598" refString="Solem, A. (1966) Some non-marine mollusks from Thailand, with notes on classification of the Helicarionidae. Spolia Zoologica Musei Hauniensis, 24, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1966">Solem, 1966</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, also has a coiled retractor caecum (
<bibRefCitation author="Solem, A." box="[1030,1178,1275,1301]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref77598" refString="Solem, A. (1966) Some non-marine mollusks from Thailand, with notes on classification of the Helicarionidae. Spolia Zoologica Musei Hauniensis, 24, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1966">Solem 1966</bibRefCitation>
). Both species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Albers" authorityYear="1860" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" genus="Sesara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Sesara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also possess a large flagellum or lime-sac (the presence of an axial filament could not be confirmed; 
<bibRefCitation author="Solem, A." box="[151,295,1355,1381]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref77598" refString="Solem, A. (1966) Some non-marine mollusks from Thailand, with notes on classification of the Helicarionidae. Spolia Zoologica Musei Hauniensis, 24, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1966">Solem 1966</bibRefCitation>
; this study), which according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Solem, A." box="[676,840,1355,1381]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref77598" refString="Solem, A. (1966) Some non-marine mollusks from Thailand, with notes on classification of the Helicarionidae. Spolia Zoologica Musei Hauniensis, 24, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1966">Solem (1966)</bibRefCitation>
, is also characteristic of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1888" box="[1128,1358,1355,1381]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Macrochlamydinae">Macrochlamydinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="96.[151,1437,995,1821]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
The possible placement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Albers" authorityYear="1860" box="[521,601,1395,1420]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" genus="Sesara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[521,601,1395,1420]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Sesara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1888" box="[643,869,1395,1421]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Macrochlamydinae">Macrochlamydinae</taxonomicName>
has obvious implications for the status of subfamily 
<taxonomicName box="[237,353,1435,1461]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Sesarinae">Sesarinae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker, H. B." box="[367,539,1435,1461]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="205 - 346" refId="ref72823" refString="Baker, H. B. (1941 a) Zonitid snails from Pacific Islands Part 3: Genera other than Microcystinae. Bernice P. Bishop Museum Bulletin, 166, 205 - 346." type="journal article" year="1941">Baker (1941a)</bibRefCitation>
divided his Helicarionini (= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bourguignat" authorityYear="1877" box="[893,1065,1435,1461]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Helicarionidae</taxonomicName>
as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hausdorf, B." box="[1248,1427,1435,1461]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="35 - 66" refId="ref74906" refString="Hausdorf, B. (1998) Phylogeny of the Limacoidea sensu lato (Gastropoda: Stylommatophora). Journal of Molluscan Studies, 64, 35 - 66." type="journal article" year="1998">Hausdorf 1998</bibRefCitation>
) into Helicarioninae, which had an epiphallic retractor caecum, and 
<taxonomicName box="[957,1072,1475,1501]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Sesarinae">Sesarinae</taxonomicName>
, which lacked such a caecum. This conclusion was presumably based on the only anatomical drawing of the 
<typeStatus box="[1105,1155,1515,1541]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Albers" authorityYear="1860" box="[1295,1375,1515,1540]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" genus="Sesara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1295,1375,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Sesara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
then available (
<bibRefCitation author="Blanford, W. T. &amp; Godwin-Austen, H. H." box="[272,675,1555,1581]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" refId="ref73103" refString="Blanford, W. T. &amp; Godwin-Austen, H. H. (1908) Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma; Mollusca, Volume 1: Testacella and Zonitidae. Taylor and Francis, London." type="book" year="1908">Blanford &amp; Godwin-Austen 1908</bibRefCitation>
), which showed no caecum. Subsequent dissections have shown the caecum to be present in that species (
<bibRefCitation author="Schileyko, A. A." box="[653,860,1595,1621]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" refId="ref76904" refString="Schileyko, A. A. (2002 b) Treatise on Recent Terrestrial Pulmonate Molluscs, Part 9: Helicarionidae, Gymnarionidae, Rhysotinidae, Ariophantidae. Ruthenica, Supplement 2, Moscow." type="book" year="2002">Schileyko 2002b</bibRefCitation>
; this study) and in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Solem 1966)" baseAuthorityName="Solem" baseAuthorityYear="1966" box="[1096,1432,1595,1621]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" genus="Sesara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="parva">
<emphasis box="[1096,1255,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Sesara parva</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Solem, A." box="[1273,1423,1595,1621]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref77598" refString="Solem, A. (1966) Some non-marine mollusks from Thailand, with notes on classification of the Helicarionidae. Spolia Zoologica Musei Hauniensis, 24, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1966">Solem 1966</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Solem, A." box="[151,312,1635,1661]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref77598" refString="Solem, A. (1966) Some non-marine mollusks from Thailand, with notes on classification of the Helicarionidae. Spolia Zoologica Musei Hauniensis, 24, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1966">Solem (1966)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hausdorf, B." box="[374,569,1635,1661]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" pagination="35 - 66" refId="ref74906" refString="Hausdorf, B. (1998) Phylogeny of the Limacoidea sensu lato (Gastropoda: Stylommatophora). Journal of Molluscan Studies, 64, 35 - 66." type="journal article" year="1998">Hausdorf (1998)</bibRefCitation>
are followed here in regarding 
<taxonomicName box="[950,1062,1635,1661]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicarionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Sesarinae">Sesarinae</taxonomicName>
as synonym of Macroclamydinae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="96.[151,1437,995,1821]" box="[195,1243,1715,1741]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
We recognise 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Godwin-Austen" authorityYear="1888" box="[360,586,1715,1741]" class="Gastropoda" family="Ariophantidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="96" pageNumber="97" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Macrochlamydinae">Macrochlamydinae</taxonomicName>
as a subfamily defined by the following key characters:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="96.[151,1437,995,1821]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Shell not reduced (most taxa) or reduced (few taxa); sole furrows distinct. Epiphallic retractor caecum usually coiled; penis retractor muscle inserts laterally on epiphallic caecum. Stimulator absent or present.</paragraph>
